{"parentUuid":"85fb354a-ce76-4082-bdf9-d9189121fb96","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a9e3842d3be64b93d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_I4BxutbiSeQ8XD3H85hZUweR","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The following code sections were retrieved:\nPath: .dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-cleanup-audit.md\n...\n    28\t- `.claude/agents/audit-scanner.md` and `.claude/agents/audit-validator.md` — Sync copies (via `make sync-dev`).\n    29\t\n    30\t**Rationale**: D-0022 Principle 1 (Evidence Integrity), direction 2: \"Audit agents should default classification status to 'unverified' until evidence is gathered, not 'classified' pending flagging.\"\n    31\t\n    32\t**Dependencies**: None (foundational for CA-002)\n    33\t**Acceptance criteria**: audit-scanner.md contains the word \"UNVERIFIED\" as a default classification state in its instructions; audit-validator.md contains explicit instructions to document absence of confirmation; both agent files have matching dev copies.\n    34\t**Risk**: Low. Agent instruction additions; no code changes; behavioral improvement only.\n    35\t\n    36\t---\n...\n    52\t\n    53\t**Dependencies**: CA-001 (epistemic stance must be established in agent instructions first)\n    54\t**Acceptance criteria**: `classify_finding()` sets `negative_evidence_documented` on zero-reference findings; executor generates a warning when the flag is absent in a REVIEW/DELETE finding; at least one test verifies the flag is set correctly.\n    55\t**Risk**: Low. Schema addition is backward-compatible (optional field); warning does not block pipeline.\n    56\t\n    57\t---\n    58\t\n    59\t## ITEM CA-003 — Typed State Transitions in Audit Pass Progression\n    60\t\n    61\t**Priority**: P1\n    62\t**Effort**: M\n    63\t**Classification**: add new code\n    64\t**patterns_not_mass**: true — adopting LW's typed inter-agent communication (RESEARCH_READY, TASK_READY, EXECUTION_COMPLETE, BLOCKED) as IC-native typed state transitions for the G-001 → G-002 → G-003 audit pass progression\n    65\t**Why not full import**: LW's typed message protocol is implemented via bash inter-process communication; IC's audit passes are Python function-to-function calls. The typed state concept is adoptable; the IPC mechanism is not.\n    66\t\n    67\t**File paths and change description**:\n    68\t- `src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/executor.py` — Define an `AuditPassState` enum with values: `PENDING`, `SCANNING`, `SCAN_COMPLETE`, `ANALYZING`, `ANALYSIS_COMPLETE`, `VALIDATING`, `DONE`, `BLOCKED`. At each pass transition (G-001 → G-002, G-002 → G-003), emit the current state to the audit logger. If a pass returns an empty result set, emit `BLOCKED` with reason.\n    69\t- `src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py` — Add `AuditPassState` to the models module export list so consuming code can reference it without importing from executor.\n    70\t\n    71\t**Rationale**: D-0022 Principle 5 (Scalable Quality Enforcement), direction 5: \"For IC components that involve sequential agent invocation (cleanup-audit's G-001 → G-002 → G-003 progression), adopt explicit typed state transitions. BLOCKED as a first-class message type prevents silent failures in agent coordination.\"\n    72\t\n    73\t**Dependencies**: CA-001, CA-002\n    74\t**Acceptance criteria**: `AuditPassState` enum exists in executor.py; BLOCKED state is emitted when a pass produces an empty result; each G-001/G-002/G-003 transition logs the current state.\n    75\t**Risk**: Medium. New enum and state emission; requires integration test across all three passes.\n    76\t\n    77\t---\n    78\t\n    79\t## ITEM CA-004 — Executor Validation Gate Before Agent Invocation\n...\n    86\t\n    87\t**File paths and change description**:\n    88\t- `src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/executor.py` — At the beginning of `execute_cleanup_audit()`, before invoking any audit pass, validate: (a) target directory exists and is readable, (b) `--batch-size` is within valid range (1–100), (c) `--focus` value is a known domain (`infrastructure|frontend|backend|all`). If validation fails, emit `AuditPassState.BLOCKED` with reason and return early (fail-fast, not fail-mid-execution).\n    89\t- `src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/commands.py` — Move CLI-level validation (Click option types) to complement executor-level validation, not replace it. Executor must re-validate inputs it receives from any call site (not only the CLI).\n...\n\nPath: .dev/releases/complete/cross-framework-deep-analysis/artifacts/improve-cleanup-audit.md\n...\n    52\t\n    53\t**Dependencies**: CA-001 (epistemic stance must be established in agent instructions first)\n    54\t**Acceptance criteria**: `classify_finding()` sets `negative_evidence_documented` on zero-reference findings; executor generates a warning when the flag is absent in a REVIEW/DELETE finding; at least one test verifies the flag is set correctly.\n    55\t**Risk**: Low. Schema addition is backward-compatible (optional field); warning does not block pipeline.\n    56\t\n    57\t---\n    58\t\n    59\t## ITEM CA-003 — Typed State Transitions in Audit Pass Progression\n...\n    66\t\n    67\t**File paths and change description**:\n    68\t- `src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/executor.py` — Define an `AuditPassState` enum with values: `PENDING`, `SCANNING`, `SCAN_COMPLETE`, `ANALYZING`, `ANALYSIS_COMPLETE`, `VALIDATING`, `DONE`, `BLOCKED`. At each pass transition (G-001 → G-002, G-002 → G-003), emit the current state to the audit logger. If a pass returns an empty result set, emit `BLOCKED` with reason.\n    69\t- `src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py` — Add `AuditPassState` to the models module export list so consuming code can reference it without importing from executor.\n    70\t\n    71\t**Rationale**: D-0022 Principle 5 (Scalable Quality Enforcement), direction 5: \"For IC components that involve sequential agent invocation (cleanup-audit's G-001 → G-002 → G-003 progression), adopt explicit typed state transitions. BLOCKED as a first-class message type prevents silent failures in agent coordination.\"\n    72\t\n    73\t**Dependencies**: CA-001, CA-002\n    74\t**Acceptance criteria**: `AuditPassState` enum exists in executor.py; BLOCKED state is emitted when a pass produces an empty result; each G-001/G-002/G-003 transition logs the current state.\n    75\t**Risk**: Medium. New enum and state emission; requires integration test across all three passes.\n    76\t\n    77\t---\n    78\t\n    79\t## ITEM CA-004 — Executor Validation Gate Before Agent Invocation\n...\n\nPath: .dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improvement-backlog.md\n...\n   307\t\n   308\t**Change description**:\n   309\tAn `AuditPassState` enum shall be defined with values: `PENDING`, `SCANNING`, `SCAN_COMPLETE`, `ANALYZING`, `ANALYSIS_COMPLETE`, `VALIDATING`, `DONE`, `BLOCKED`. The executor shall emit current state at each G-001 → G-002 → G-003 transition and emit `BLOCKED` with reason on empty result set. `AuditPassState` shall be added to the models module export list.\n   310\t\n   311\tFiles:\n   312\t- `src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/executor.py` — add `AuditPassState` enum; emit states at transitions; emit BLOCKED with reason on empty result\n   313\t- `src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py` — add `AuditPassState` to module export list\n...\n\nPath: .dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/strategy-ic-cleanup-audit.md\n...\n    30\t\n    31\tEach step is supervised by `CleanupAuditProcess` (`src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/process.py:22`), which extends `_PipelineClaudeProcess` and writes output to NDJSON files. The `OutputMonitor` detects stalled processes (zero byte growth) and `error_max_turns` signals from the NDJSON stream.\n    32\t\n    33\t**Classification engine**: `classify_finding()` (`src/superclaude/cli/audit/classification.py:110`) is a pure-Python deterministic function that maps `(has_references, is_test_or_config, is_temporal_artifact)` inputs to a `(V2Tier, V2Action, V1Category, confidence)` result. The two-tier system (Tier-1 actionable: DELETE/INVESTIGATE; Tier-2 informational: KEEP/REORGANIZE) maps deterministically to legacy v1 categories via `TIER_TO_V1_MAP`.\n...\n\nPath: .dev/releases/complete/cross-framework-deep-analysis/artifacts/improvement-backlog.md\n...\n   307\t\n   308\t**Change description**:\n   309\tAn `AuditPassState` enum shall be defined with values: `PENDING`, `SCANNING`, `SCAN_COMPLETE`, `ANALYZING`, `ANALYSIS_COMPLETE`, `VALIDATING`, `DONE`, `BLOCKED`. The executor shall emit current state at each G-001 → G-002 → G-003 transition and emit `BLOCKED` with reason on empty result set. `AuditPassState` shall be added to the models module export list.\n   310\t\n   311\tFiles:\n   312\t- `src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/executor.py` — add `AuditPassState` enum; emit states at transitions; emit BLOCKED with reason on empty result\n   313\t- `src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py` — add `AuditPassState` to module export list\n...\n\nPath: .dev/releases/complete/cross-framework-deep-analysis/artifacts/D-0034/spec.md\n...\n   248\t\n   249\t#### CA-003 — Typed State Transitions in Audit Pass Progression\n   250\t**Component**: Cleanup-Audit CLI | **Effort**: M | **Classification**: add new code\n   251\t**patterns_not_mass**: true — LW typed inter-agent communication adopted; bash IPC rejected\n   252\t\n   253\t**Change description**:\n   254\t- `src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/executor.py` — Define `AuditPassState` enum: `PENDING`, `SCANNING`, `SCAN_COMPLETE`, `ANALYZING`, `ANALYSIS_COMPLETE`, `VALIDATING`, `DONE`, `BLOCKED`. Emit state at each G-001 → G-002 → G-003 transition. Emit `BLOCKED` with reason on empty result set.\n   255\t- `src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py` — Add `AuditPassState` to models module export list.\n...\n\nPath: .dev/releases/complete/cross-framework-deep-analysis/artifacts/strategy-ic-cleanup-audit.md\n...\n    30\t\n    31\tEach step is supervised by `CleanupAuditProcess` (`src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/process.py:22`), which extends `_PipelineClaudeProcess` and writes output to NDJSON files. The `OutputMonitor` detects stalled processes (zero byte growth) and `error_max_turns` signals from the NDJSON stream.\n    32\t\n    33\t**Classification engine**: `classify_finding()` (`src/superclaude/cli/audit/classification.py:110`) is a pure-Python deterministic function that maps `(has_references, is_test_or_config, is_temporal_artifact)` inputs to a `(V2Tier, V2Action, V1Category, confidence)` result. The two-tier system (Tier-1 actionable: DELETE/INVESTIGATE; Tier-2 informational: KEEP/REORGANIZE) maps deterministically to legacy v1 categories via `TIER_TO_V1_MAP`.\n...\n\nPath: .dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md\n     1\t---\n     2\trelease: wiring-verification-gate-v1.0\n     3\tversion: 1.0.0\n     4\tstatus: draft\n     5\tdate: 2026-03-17\n     6\tparent_analysis: cli-portify-executor-noop-forensic-report.md\n     7\tparent_ranking: proposal-ranking.md\n     8\tfidelity_link: \"Link 3: Tasklist -> Code\"\n     9\tpriority: P0\n    10\testimated_scope: 300-400 lines production code\n    11\t---\n    12\t\n    13\t# Wiring Verification Gate v1.0 -- Release Specification\n    14\t\n    15\t## 1. Problem Statement\n...\n   552\t\n   553\tif config.wiring_gate_mode == \"shadow\":\n   554\t    # Log result but do not affect task status\n   555\t    logger.info(f\"[shadow] Wiring gate: {report.total_findings} findings\")\n   556\telif config.wiring_gate_mode == \"soft\":\n   557\t    # Warn in TUI but do not block\n   558\t    if not report.passed:\n   559\t        tui.warn(f\"Wiring gate: {report.total_findings} findings\")\n   560\telif config.wiring_gate_mode == \"full\":\n   561\t    # Block task completion\n   562\t    passed, reason = gate_passed(wiring_report_path, WIRING_GATE)\n   563\t    if not passed:\n   564\t        # Trigger remediation via SprintGatePolicy\n   565\t        ...\n   566\t```\n...\n   735\t\n   736\t- Wiring analysis runs after every task in sprint execution\n   737\t- Results logged to `.sprint-state/wiring/` directory\n   738\t- No impact on task status or pipeline flow\n   739\t- Collect baseline: false positive rate, finding distribution, analysis time\n   740\t\n   741\t### Phase 2: Soft (release +1, pending shadow data review)\n   742\t\n   743\t- Findings surfaced as warnings in sprint TUI\n   744\t- Findings recorded in `DeferredRemediationLog`\n   745\t- Block only at release scope (per `resolve_gate_mode()` which returns BLOCKING for release)\n   746\t- Override available via `--skip-wiring-gate` flag\n   747\t\n   748\t**Threshold calibration for known FPR sources**:\n   749\t\n   750\tWhen setting Phase 2 activation thresholds from Phase 1 baseline data,\n   751\texplicitly account for the following known false-positive sources:\n...\n   867\t\n   868\t| SC | Description | Verification |\n   869\t|----|-------------|-------------|\n   870\t| SC-001 | Wiring gate detects `Optional[Callable] = None` never provided at call site | Unit test: `test_detect_unwired_callable_basic` |\n   871\t| SC-002 | Wiring gate detects orphan modules in `steps/` directories | Unit test: `test_detect_orphan_module` |\n   872\t| SC-003 | Wiring gate detects unresolvable registry entries | Unit test: `test_detect_unwired_registry` |\n   873\t| SC-004 | Report conforms to `GateCriteria` validation pattern | Unit test: `test_gate_passes_clean_report` |\n   874\t| SC-005 | `gate_passed()` evaluates `WIRING_GATE` without modification | Integration test: `test_cli_portify_fixture` |\n...\n   927\t| T06 | Unit tests for T02-T04 + test fixtures | `tests/audit/test_wiring_gate.py` (minimum 14 unit tests per Section 9.1), `tests/audit/fixtures/` (SC-010 fixture structure per Section 9.2 behavioral contract) | T02, T03, T04 |\n   928\t| T07 | Sprint integration (shadow mode hook) | `sprint/executor.py` (modify), `sprint/config.py` (modify) | T05 |\n   929\t| T08 | Deviation count reconciliation | `roadmap/gates.py` (modify) | -- |\n   930\t| T09 | Unit tests for T08 | `tests/audit/test_deviation_recon.py` | T08 |\n   931\t| T10 | Integration test: cli-portify fixture | `tests/audit/test_wiring_integration.py` | T06, T07 |\n   932\t| T11 | Retrospective: run against actual `cli_portify/` | Validation report | T10 |\n   933\t\n   934\t**Critical path**: T01 -> T02/T03/T04 (parallel) -> T05 -> T06 -> T07 -> T10 -> T11\n...\n\nPath: .dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md\n     1\t# Anti-Instincts Gate -- Unified Specification\n     2\t\n     3\t<!-- Source: Merge (new content bridging V2+V5) -->\n     4\t\n     5\t> **Status**: Design Spec -- Ready for Implementation\n     6\t> **Created**: 2026-03-17\n     7\t> **Protocol**: sc:adversarial Step 5 (Merge Execution)\n     8\t> **Co-bases**: V2 (7.60) + V5 (7.55)\n     9\t> **Cherry-picks**: V4-2 (Fingerprints), V1-C (Spec Structural Audit), V1-D+V5-2 (Prompt Constraint)\n    10\t> **Target module**: `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/`\n    11\t> **Pipeline latency added**: <1s (all checks are pure Python)\n    12\t> **LLM calls added**: 0\n    13\t\n    14\t---\n    15\t\n    16\t## 1. Problem Statement\n    17\t\n    18\t<!-- Source: Merge (new content bridging V2+V5) -->\n...\n   947\t\n   948\t### Enforcement Strategy\n   949\t\n   950\t<!-- Source: V1-C (spec structural audit), adapted per refactor-plan -->\n   951\t\n   952\tPhase 1 (immediate): Warning-only. The executor logs a warning if the ratio falls below 0.5 but does not block the pipeline. This allows shadow-mode validation on real specs before enforcement.\n   953\t\n   954\tPhase 2 (after validation): STRICT enforcement. If the structural count suggests the extraction is missing significant content, the executor re-triggers extraction or halts with an actionable error.\n   955\t\n   956\t---\n   957\t\n   958\t## 8. Gate Definition\n   959\t\n   960\t<!-- Source: Merge (new content bridging V2+V5) -->\n   961\t\n   962\t### New Gate: `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE`\n   963\t\n   964\t**File**: `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/gates.py` (modify existing)\n   965\t\n   966\t```python\n   967\t# --- Anti-Instinct Gate check functions ---\n...\n   999\t\n  1000\t\n  1001\tdef _fingerprint_coverage_check(content: str) -> bool:\n  1002\t    \"\"\"Verify spec code-level identifiers have sufficient roadmap coverage.\n  1003\t\n  1004\t    This check requires both spec and roadmap content. Since semantic\n  1005\t    checks receive only a single content string, the real enforcement\n  1006\t    happens in the executor. This validates the executor's written result.\n  1007\t    \"\"\"\n  1008\t    fm = _parse_frontmatter(content)\n  1009\t    if fm is None:\n  1010\t        return False\n  1011\t    try:\n  1012\t        return float(fm.get(\"fingerprint_coverage\", 0.0)) >= 0.7\n  1013\t    except (ValueError, TypeError):\n  1014\t        return False\n  1015\t\n  1016\t\n  1017\t# --- Gate definition ---\n  1018\t\n  1019\tANTI_INSTINCT_GATE = GateCriteria(\n  1020\t    required_frontmatter_fields=[\n  1021\t        \"undischarged_obligations\",    # V2-A: integer count\n  1022\t        \"uncovered_contracts\",         # V5-1: integer count\n  1023\t        \"fingerprint_coverage\",        # V4-2: float 0.0-1.0\n  1024\t    ],\n...\n  1395\t\n  1396\t| File | Changes | Source |\n  1397\t|---|---|---|\n  1398\t| `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/gates.py` | Add `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE` definition with 3 semantic checks; add 3 check functions (`_no_undischarged_obligations`, `_integration_contracts_covered`, `_fingerprint_coverage_check`); update `ALL_GATES` list to insert `(\"anti-instinct\", ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE)` between `merge` and `test-strategy` | V2-A + V5-1 + V4-2 |\n  1399\t| `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/executor.py` | Add anti-instinct step to `_build_steps()`; add structural audit hook after extract (`_run_structural_audit`); add `_run_anti_instinct_audit()` function; add import for `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE`; update `_get_all_step_ids()` to include `\"anti-instinct\"` | All |\n...\n\nPath: .dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md\n...\n    16\t\n    17\t### 0.3 Citation rule used\n    18\tCritical claims cite source file + section label. If section labels are absent, file heading context is used.\n    19\t\n    20\t---\n    21\t\n    22\t## 1. Release Scope and Goals\n    23\t\n    24\t### 1.1 Scope\n    25\tImplement a unified audit-gating capability that blocks completion/release transitions unless the corresponding gate passes at three scopes:\n    26\t1. Task gate\n    27\t2. Milestone gate\n    28\t3. Release gate\n    29\t\n    30\t(Source: `01-requirements-spec.md` → Goal; Task-Level Gate; Milestone-Level Gate; Release-Level Gate)\n    31\t\n    32\t### 1.2 Primary goals\n    33\t1. Deterministic pass/fail gating with evidence-backed outputs\n    34\t2. Explicit audit workflow states for all scopes\n    35\t3. Single primary user interface (`/sc:audit-gate`)\n    36\t4. Rollout-safe enforcement (shadow → soft → full)\n...\n   320\t\n   321\t(Source: `05-review-checklist.md` → Section 10; `executive-summary.md` → critical decisions; `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md`)\n   322\t\n   323\t---\n   324\t\n   325\t## 10. Implementation Mapping\n   326\t\n   327\t### 10.1 Phase plan\n   328\t- **Phase 0**: design/policy lock and owner/date assignments\n   329\t- **Phase 1**: deterministic contracts + evaluator + transition validator\n   330\t- **Phase 2**: runtime controls (lease/heartbeat/retry/recovery)\n   331\t- **Phase 3**: sprint CLI integration + override governance flow + report persistence\n   332\t- **Phase 4**: rollout execution + KPI gates + rollback drills\n   333\t\n   334\t(Source: `implementation-plan-v1.2.md`)\n   335\t\n   336\t### 10.2 File-level change map (implementation target)\n   337\t1. `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/models.py` — states/enums/constraints/profile fields\n   338\t2. `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/tui.py` — completion/release guards and operator guidance\n   339\t3. `src/superclaude/skills/sc-audit-gate/SKILL.md` — command behavior/profile/output contract\n   340\t4. `src/superclaude/skills/sc-audit-gate-protocol/SKILL.md` — deterministic evaluator and transition legality/recovery flow\n   341\t5. `src/superclaude/agents/*.md` — enrichment-only role clarification\n   342\t6. `tests/sprint/test_audit_gate_state_machine.py` — legal/illegal transitions + stuck-state recovery\n   343\t7. `tests/sprint/test_audit_gate_profiles.py` — profile determinism + severity behavior\n...\n   370\t| 5. Tier model soundness | PASS (conditional) | Finalize numeric thresholds + major severity behavior | `checklist-outcome-v1.2.md` |\n "}]}]},"uuid":"9d8412ab-8c49-4394-9462-470ce2827e1a","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:47:35.427Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"85fb354a-ce76-4082-bdf9-d9189121fb96","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
