{"parentUuid":"66cd3f4d-5ebc-4449-905b-47d63fdbc60f","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a9e3842d3be64b93d","message":{"id":"resp_0fe05764326dc8b40169b9a1ea7e14819aae4eaf8553a68c3d","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"gpt-5.4","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":48793,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":2320,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Compared `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-cleanup-audit.md` against the three refactor specs. Overall result: the two evidence-integrity items remain mostly independent, while the two executor/state-machine items need alignment with v3.1’s audit-gating model.\n\n**ITEM CA-001** — Presumption of Falsehood in Audit Agent Instructions  \n- Status: UNAFFECTED  \n- Evidence:  \n  - Assigned item targets cleanup-audit agent instructions in `src/superclaude/agents/audit-scanner.md` and `src/superclaude/agents/audit-validator.md` with explicit `UNVERIFIED` defaulting and “document absence of evidence” behavior (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-cleanup-audit.md:17-34`).  \n  - v3.0 wiring gate is scoped to `src/superclaude/cli/audit/wiring_gate.py`, `src/superclaude/cli/audit/wiring_config.py`, `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/config.py`, `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/executor.py`, and `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/gates.py` — no cleanup-audit agents or audit-agent instruction model (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md`, Sections 3.2, 5, 12).  \n  - v3.05 anti-instincts is explicitly targeted at `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/` and `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/executor.py`, not cleanup-audit agents (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:10`, `1398-1399`).  \n  - v3.1 mentions `src/superclaude/agents/*.md` only as “enrichment-only role clarification,” with implementation centered on sprint models/TUI/skills/tests, not cleanup-audit epistemic instructions (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:336-347`).  \n- Recommendation: KEEP-AS-IS\n\n**ITEM CA-002** — Mandatory Negative Evidence Documentation  \n- Status: UNAFFECTED  \n- Evidence:  \n  - CA-002 adds cleanup-audit-specific schema/classification/reporting fields: `negative_evidence` in `scanner_schema.py`, `negative_evidence_documented` in `classification.py`, and executor warnings in `cleanup_audit/executor.py` (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-cleanup-audit.md:38-55`).  \n  - v3.0 wiring gate adds a separate code-wiring report and `WIRING_GATE` contract; it does not modify cleanup-audit finding schema/classification (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md`, Sections 4.1-4.4, 5).  \n  - v3.05 anti-instincts concerns roadmap extraction/integration/fingerprint omissions and `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE`, not cleanup-audit finding evidence fields (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md`, Sections 1 and 8).  \n  - v3.1 does require evidence-backed outputs and evidence refs for failed checks (`Sections 1.2, 5.3`), but at the unified sprint gate-result layer; it does not define CA-002’s negative-evidence field or zero-reference audit-finding behavior (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:32-38`, `174-181`, `187-200`).  \n- Recommendation: KEEP-AS-IS\n\n**ITEM CA-003** — Typed State Transitions in Audit Pass Progression  \n- Status: OVERLAPPING  \n- Evidence:  \n  - CA-003 proposes a cleanup-audit-local `AuditPassState` enum in `src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/executor.py` with states `PENDING`, `SCANNING`, `SCAN_COMPLETE`, `ANALYZING`, `ANALYSIS_COMPLETE`, `VALIDATING`, `DONE`, `BLOCKED`, plus transition logging and export through `src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py` (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-cleanup-audit.md:59-75`).  \n  - v3.1 independently makes “explicit audit workflow states” a primary goal and defines an authoritative legal/illegal state machine using sprint-scope states like `ready_for_audit_task`, `audit_task_running`, `audit_task_passed`, `audit_task_failed`, etc. (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:32-38`, `98-152`).  \n  - v3.1 also requires a `GateTransitionEvent` schema and a transition validator, with implementation targeting sprint models and audit-gate protocol logic (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:213-225`, `325-347`).  \n  - This is overlap rather than direct contradiction because v3.1’s state machine is for task/milestone/release audit gating in sprint flow, while CA-003 is for internal G-001→G-002→G-003 cleanup-audit pass progression. But CA-003’s standalone enum would create a second audit-state vocabulary unless aligned.  \n  - v3.0 and v3.05 do not materially affect this item; their scopes are wiring verification and roadmap anti-instinct gates respectively.  \n- Recommendation: REVISE — keep the typed-transition concept, but rename/reframe it as cleanup-audit internal pass states and map it explicitly to v3.1’s broader audit-gating event/state model instead of introducing an unqualified parallel audit-state contract in shared models.\n\n**ITEM CA-004** — Executor Validation Gate Before Agent Invocation  \n- Status: OVERLAPPING  \n- Evidence:  \n  - CA-004 adds cleanup-audit executor preflight validation in `src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/executor.py` and complementary validation in `src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/commands.py`, returning early with `AuditPassState.BLOCKED` on invalid input (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-cleanup-audit.md:79-95`).  \n  - v3.1 Phase 3 explicitly adds “sprint CLI integration + override governance flow + report persistence,” and its checklist closure requires integrating a deterministic transition validator before completion transitions (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:327-355`, `372-375`).  \n  - v3.1 Section 10.2’s file map does not touch `src/superclaude/cli/cleanup_audit/executor.py`; it targets `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/models.py`, `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/tui.py`, skills, agents, and sprint tests (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md:336-347`).  \n  - So the overlap is conceptual: both introduce fail-fast validation/blocking before invalid transitions/execution continue, but v3.1 does so at sprint audit-gate transition level, not cleanup-audit executor input validation.  \n  - v3.0’s sprint integration modifies `src/superclaude/cli/sprint/executor.py` for wiring analysis hook, not cleanup-audit validation (`/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md:537-572`, `594-600`, `927-929`).  \n  - v3.05 is roadmap-only and unrelated.  \n- Recommendation: REVISE — retain executor-level revalidation, but align its failure signaling with v3.1’s deterministic failure/transition vocabulary instead of depending solely on CA-003’s standalone `AuditPassState.BLOCKED` design.\n\nOverall, `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-cleanup-audit.md` remains largely valid after the three refactors: CA-001 and CA-002 stand independently and should remain, while CA-003 and CA-004 are not obsolete but should be updated to integrate with v3.1’s authoritative sprint audit-gating state/transition model so cleanup-audit does not introduce a competing audit-state language or blocking contract."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn"},"type":"assistant","uuid":"dd967dd5-dd5d-486d-9786-5258c642cfa7","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:53.802Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
